text: Why do Java developers wear glasses? Because they can’t C#.
I told my computer I needed a break… it froze.
Debugging is like being the detective in a crime movie where you are also the murderer.
Why did the neural network go to therapy? Too many unresolved layers.
My data went on a date… now it’s an outlier.
Why did the variable break up with the constant? It needed some change.
I told my boss I made a machine that turns stupidity into money… he said, 'Great, call it a meeting.'
Parallel lines have so much in common. It’s a shame they’ll never meet.
I told my girlfriend she drew her eyebrows too high — she looked surprised.
Why don’t skeletons fight each other? They don’t have the guts.
I asked Siri why I’m single — she opened the front camera.
Why do programmers like dark mode? Because light attracts bugs.
My Wi-Fi went down for five minutes, so I had to talk to my family. They seem nice.
Why did the math book look sad? Too many problems.
Why don’t bachelors like Git? They’re afraid of commits.
Why did the chicken join the band? It had drumsticks.
Why did the PowerPoint cross the road? To get to the other slide.
I made a pencil with two erasers — it was pointless.
Why do statisticians love cats? They always land on their mean.
I told my laptop a joke about RAM… it still hasn’t processed it.
Why did the scarecrow win an award? Because he was outstanding in his field.
Why don’t robots panic? Because they have nerves of steel.
I asked my AI to tell me a joke — it started training for three hours.
Why was the computer cold? It left its Windows open.
Why did the AI dump its partner? Low correlation.
Why do JavaScript developers hate the ocean? It has too many callbacks.
Why was the calendar popular? It had a lot of dates.
Why did the student eat his homework? The teacher said it was a piece of cake.
Why can’t your nose be twelve inches long? Because then it’d be a foot.
My roommate thinks onions are the only food that makes you cry, so I threw a coconut at him.
